description: Core always-on project rule for completion-first Codex behavior
alwaysApply: true
---

Read `AGENTS.md` and all files in `docs/` before making implementation decisions.

Operate in completion-first mode:
- complete all non-blocked work
- preserve architecture unless the repo is effectively empty
- never hallucinate MCP or external results
- do not stop early because one dependency fails
- leave a structured residual task list for blocked work

Critical product rules:
- retrieval is the source of truth
- deterministic logic decides inclusion where fields exist
- no surfaced result without citation and canonical source link
- unknown fields remain unknown
- keep storage lean and privacy-conscious
